SIMPLE: hasten
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hasten
<hw>Has"ten</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧s"'n)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Hastened</conjf>
<pr>(h⟦amac⟧s"'nd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hastening</conjf> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧s"'n*⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<def>To press; to drive or urge forward; to push on; to precipitate; to
accelerate the movement of; to expedite; to hurry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would <qex>hasten</qex> my escape from the windy storm.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. lv. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hasten</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hasten
<hw>Has"ten</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To move with celerity; to be
rapid in motion; to act speedily or quickly; to go quickly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>hastened</qex> to the spot whence the noise came.</q>
<rj><qau>De Foe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hastener</ent>⟦br⟧
